From: Eli Barzilay <eli@barzilay.org>
To: Robby Findler <robby@eecs.northwestern.edu>
Cc: "bugs@racket-lang.org" <bugs@racket-lang.org>,
        "bug-notification@racket-lang.org" <bug-notification@racket-lang.org>
Subject: Re: [racket-bug] all/12423: Long menu entry
Date: Tue, 6 Dec 2011 15:56:41 -0500

 Yesterday, Robby Findler wrote:
 > I think it should be (roughly) of the form 'verb noun'.  "Use
 > vertical layout" seems too vague and "Use vertical
 > definitions/interactions layout" is clunky and maybe still too long?
 > Or do you like those? Or something else?
 
 I don't see a problem with dropping the "use" verb -- there are plenty
 of verb-less examples like "Preferences", "New Tab", "Page Setup",
 etc.  But even with it, or with Matthias's suggestion, it would be
 much better than the current label.
 
 BTW, I like "Use vertical layout" more than "Align windows
 vertically", since it's unclear which windows the second is talking
 about so I prefer the more vague option.  So the summary is that my
 ordered preferences for current suggestions are:
 
   * Vertical layout
   * Use vertical layout
   * Align windows vertically
   * Use vertical definitions/interactions layout
 
 (And no, I didn't order them by length, although it turned out that
 way...)
 
 -- 
           ((lambda (x) (x x)) (lambda (x) (x x)))          Eli Barzilay:
                     http://barzilay.org/                   Maze is Life!
